node.text:
I’m so pleased to be part of the #sharethemicfoodandbev campaign, and, indeed, to be sharing the mic with the fabulous @zoeadjonyoh, chef, author and activist and author of Zoe’s Ghana Kitchen. What ‘sharing the mic’ means here is that Zoe will be taking over my Instagram account for 24 hours from 12 midday tomorrow, Monday the 20th, to 12 midday on Tuesday July 21st. You are in for a treat! 
This is a campaign dedicated to amplifying the voices of Black women whose contributions to the food culture have been customarily overlooked, and it’s a real honour to #keepsharingthemic

node.text:
I’ve made a video-selfie with details of how to make my Emergency Brownies for #hopefromhome on #worldhealthday in support of health workers and medical teams. I know that many of you who would like to donate are just not able to right now, but if you can please do, by going to hopefromhome.tiltify.com.
.
#recipeoftheday

Well, I’m thrilled to say that this week we have @chetnamakan’s 30-Minute Indian on #CookbookCorner. To read  all about it and get the recipe for her fast and fabulous Butter Chicken, click on link in bio.
.

What I mean by this, is that you tap on my name, which will take you to a page that has a link on it that says www.nigella.com/instagram. When you click on this link, it will take you to a page of photographs: click on the photograph you want the recipe of, and you will be taken to it! 
.
Photography by @nassimarothacker

#RecipeOfTheDay is this dark beauty: Baby Aubergines/Eggplant with Oregano and Red Onions. And should this be of interest – and even if it isn’t! – it happens to be #vegan. Not surprising, of course, since it’s a vegetable dish! And a divine one, at that 
.

And to get the recipe, either go to nigella.com or click on link in bio. What I mean by this, is that you tap on my name, which will take you to a page that has a link on it that says www.nigella.com/instagram. When you click on this link, it will take you to a page of photographs: click on the photograph you want the recipe of, and you will be taken to it!
.
Photograph by @petrinatinslay 
#nigellissima 
.

And to get the recipe, click on link in bio. What I mean by this, is that you tap on my name, which will take you to a page that has a link on it that says www.nigella.com/instagram. node.text:
I’m really sorry to be so hideously late with #RecipeOfTheDay. It’s a great favourite: Italian Roast Chicken with Peppers and Olives (and I sometimes add a tumble of unpeeled garlic cloves to the pan, too). And if you don’t eat meat, I must tell you that by using more of all the leeks and peppers etc, and leaving out the chicken (and you could scatter feta over at the end, once it’s cooked) it is a divine vegetable dish
.

And to get the recipe, either go to nigella.com or click on link in bio. node.text:
Continuing my feasting from yesterday’s haul from @rex.goldsmith, butterflied sardines (cooked quickly in a very hot oven, with olive oil, garlic, chilli flakes, orange zest, and a spritz of lemon) with a watercress and red chicory salad, with toasted pine nuts and dill. I probably should have grilled the sardines, and I certainly overdressed the salad, but it was just lovely all the same.

It’s not on the floor, by the way, although it does rather look like that: it’s the slightly worn slate-topped table I have in the garden!

#RecipeOfTheDay is a lazy delight: No-Churn Margarita Ice Cream! The metric measurements for the booze seem to be missing in the ingredients, though: the 2 tablespoons of tequila = 30ml; the 3 tablespoons Cointreau (or Triple Sec or Grand Marnier) = 45ml. Have fun!
